            <person xml:id="pers1420">
               <p><persName>George Merryweather</persName> was a merchant in
                     <placeName>Yarm</placeName> on Tees, who in the late <date>1740</date>s became
                  an active promoter and generous patron of Methodism, especially within the
                  extensive <placeName>Yarm</placeName> circuit. On <date when="1764-04-30">Apr. 30,
                     1764</date>, he married <persName>Susannah Suggett</persName>, of
                     <placeName>Hutton Rudby, Yorkshire</placeName>. See <hi rend="italic">WHS</hi>
                  44 (<date when="1983">1983</date>): 47, 80–81; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Dictionary</hi>, 229–30.</p>
            </person>
